2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new OOD detection scheme based on Random Network Distillation (RND) and evaluates its performance against baseline OOD detectors. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new approach to OOD detection that utilizes blurred images during training and achieves better performance than baseline methods. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper utilizes neural network-based approaches for OOD detection and proposes a novel method that improves upon existing techniques. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the vulnerability of conventional OOD detection schemes to blurred images, which could have implications for security and privacy in image datasets.
